File	Purpose
connection.php	Establishes connection to the MySQL database.
ecommerce_db.sql	SQL script to create and populate the ecommerce_db database.
index.php	Homepage with jQuery effects and product listing.
products.php	Displays products dynamically from the database.


🛠 Setup Instructions
Import Database

Open phpMyAdmin (via XAMPP).

Create a new database named ecommerce_db.

Import ecommerce_db.sql.

Configure Connection

Update connection.php with your MySQL credentials:

php
$conn = mysqli_connect("localhost", "root", "", "ecommerce_db");
Run the Project

Place the Lab09 folder inside htdocs (XAMPP).

Start Apache and MySQL in XAMPP.

Open in browser:

Code
http://localhost/Lab09/index.php
🎯 Learning Outcomes
By completing this lab, students will:

Understand jQuery effects (hide/show, fade, slide, etc.).

Connect PHP to a MySQL database.

Display products dynamically using SQL queries.

Build a simple interactive e‑commerce demo.
